extends layout.pug

block content
  main.page
    article.prose
      header.prose-header
        p.eyebrow Playground
        h1 Watch the CRDT do its thing
      section
        p.lede Two simulated peers, side by side. Drag the latency slider, drop packets, mash the keyboard. The document always converges.
        .placeholder-card
          p.placeholder-title Coming up next
          p This page will host an interactive CRDT visualizer:
          ul
            li Two mini editors, each running its own CRDT instance
            li A network simulator between them — adjustable latency and packet loss
            li An internals overlay showing operation queues, fractional identifiers, and version vector state in real time
            li An auto-chaos button that types random characters on both sides under whatever network conditions you set
            li A convergence checksum — turns green when both sides match (which they always will)
          p For now: open #[a.external(href='/') the editor] in two browser tabs to see the same algorithm running over real WebRTC.
